[1] Canada (British Columbia, Vancouver)
Date: Wed 4 Jul 2018, 2:47 PM PDT
Source: CTV News [edited]
https://bc.ctvnews.ca/yvr-passengers-may-have-been-exposed-to-measles-bccdc-1.4000110


Public health officials are warning passengers who recently flew from India to Vancouver or passed through the local airport that they may have been exposed to measles. An infectious individual is known to have taken 2 flights last month [June 2018], 1st from New Delhi to Guangzhou, from Guangzhou on to Vancouver.

Those who took China Southern flights CZ 3028, which departed [23 Jun 2018] at 11:55 AM, or CZ 377, which departed [24 Jun 2018] at 12:50 AM, may have come in contact with the virus. In addition, BC Centre for Disease Control said anyone who was at the Vancouver International Airport on [Sat 23 Jun 2018] after 9:30 PM should be wary.

As some of the passengers and flight crew may have travelled on to other destinations in Canada, the BCCDC is also warning Canadian and Pacific Northwest public health officials of the case.

Travellers are asked to check their immunization status. The majority will be immune, but those including infants and people who haven't been given the vaccine are at risk. Symptoms can show up between a week and 2 weeks after exposure - in this case by about [15 Jul 2018].

[Byline: Kendra Mangione]

