[4] France (New Aquitaine)
Date: Fri 6 Jul 2018
Source: France Info [in French, trans. Corr.SB, edited]
https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/nouvelle-aquitaine/gironde/bordeaux/rougeole-deces-fille-17-ans-au-chu-bordeaux-1508097.html


A 17-year-old girl died at Bordeaux University Hospital following neurological complications related to measles. This is the 2nd death caused by measles in New Aquitaine, the 3rd in France since November [2017]. The patient is said to be from the region, but it's not know where she contracted the disease . With less than 10 confirmed cases per month, New Aquitaine is no longer in an epidemic phase, but many vulnerable people are still not vaccinated. If the threat has been curbed, it must continue to prevent to avoid a possible return.

Nearly half of the cases in France come from New Aquitaine

According to the Regional Health Agency (ARS), since [6 Nov 2017], 1096 cases of measles were confirmed (2567 in France) in New Aquitaine. This represents almost half of the cases in France, 1 in 4 cases required hospitalization, 12 patients were transferred to intensive care and 2 died. Nearly 90 percent of these cases were not or insufficiently vaccinated, as 2 doses are needed to be fully protected.

The ARS asks people to check their vaccination and, if in doubt, to get vaccinated. Measles can lead to respiratory and neurological complications that can have serious consequences.

[Relatives of unprotected individuals] are also vulnerable to since the disease is very contagious: 1 person can infect up to 20 people. Especially fragile people such as children under 1 year and immunocompromised people cannot be vaccinated [so can only be protected by herd immunity when a high enough proportion of the population living around them is immune. - Mod.LK]

There is no cure for the disease, only drugs to relieve the symptoms. The most effective solution is to get vaccinated to prevent spread.

2nd death in New Aquitaine
--------------------------

In June [2018], a 26-year-old patient died of the disease. And last February [2018], a 32-year-old mother who was not vaccinated died at CHU [Centres Hospitaliers Régionaux et Universitaires] Poitiers.

The MMR (measles-mumps-rubella) vaccine is now mandatory for children born after 1 Jan 2018. The 2nd dose that is administered later guarantees immunity.

[Byline: Alexandre Muffon Cattin]

